  <title>viennaCMS, from start to finish</title>

  <chapter>
    <title>Introduction</title>

    <section>
      <title>Why this document was written</title>

      <para>This document is written for the user who wants to use viennaCMS,
      and maybe even develop for it. It will take you from the beginning of
      viennaCMS, to the point of developing for it.</para>
    </section>
  </chapter>

  <chapter>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <section>
      <title>Needed software</title>

      <para>viennaCMS does not really need that much special software
      applications. Actually, the only things that are really required
      are:</para>

      <itemizedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para>A web server, such as Apache, Lighttpd or IIS. We recommend
          Apache or Lighttpd, by the way, as they support nice URLs.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>PHP 5.2.0 or higher installed on the web server.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>A MySQL 5.0 or higer database. Other database types will be
          supported in future versions.</para>
        </listitem>
      </itemizedlist>

      <para>After you are sure your web host supports these, you can continue
      to the next step.</para>
    </section>

    <section>
      <title>Installation, step-by-step</title>

      <para>These instructions guide you step-by-step through the installation
      of viennaCMS. Please note that you already need to have a web site on a
      host that supports all of the above. Also, a database needs to be
      already created, and you should know the database host, username,
      password and name.</para>

      <orderedlist>
        <listitem>
          <para>Extract the .zip archive of viennaCMS. After that, upload the
          contents of the viennacms-VERSION folder to your web site.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>If needed on your web host, change the permissions of
          config.php, the files folder and the cache folder to be writable for
          the web server. On a normal webhost, you should CHMOD them to
          777.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>Go to your web site url, where you uploaded viennaCMS. For
          example: http://yoursite.test/viennacms/ or
          http://mysite.invalid/</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>You will see the installation wizard. In the first step, you
          will see if you meet all the requirements for running viennaCMS. If
          the Next button is available, click it.</para>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>You will see a long list of form fields. I will step over all
          of them in just a moment:</para>

          <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
              <para><emphasis role="bold">Database server:</emphasis> the host
              name where your database is located. Most web hosts use
              localhost.</para>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
              <para><emphasis role="bold">Database username:</emphasis> the
              user name of your database. You already have this one from
              before the wizard started.</para>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
              <para><emphasis role="bold">Database password:</emphasis> the
              password which belongs to the user.</para>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
              <para><emphasis role="bold">Database name:</emphasis> the
              database you created before starting the installation.</para>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
              <para><emphasis role="bold">Table prefix:</emphasis> if this is
              the only viennaCMS installation in the database, don't change
              it.</para>
            </listitem>

            <listitem>
              <para><emphasis role="bold">Admin information:</emphasis> the
              user name and password for access to the administration
              panel.</para>
            </listitem>
          </itemizedlist>
        </listitem>

        <listitem>
          <para>After entering all of those, click Next. You will now,
          hopefully, see that the installation is finished. If so, click Next,
          to go to your new web site!</para>
        </listitem>
      </orderedlist>
    </section>
  </chapter>

